A fatal auto crash that occurred in Tungan Maje area of the Federal Capital Territory has claimed six persons leaving nine people injured. The accident which happened around 10 am on Friday was reported to have been caused by a truck that lost control and later rammed into a commercial vehicle. According to reports, five people died on the spot while a passenger later died on the way to the hospital. Jealous Lover Kills Girlfriend For Flirting With Customer In… Lassa Fever Kills 40 Persons In 30 Days – NCDC Three passengers were said to have escaped unhurt. The FCT Sector Commander of the Federal Road Safety Corps, Ogar Ochi, who confirmed the accident said it was caused by over-speeding. He said, “18 people were involved in the accident. Six have been confirmed dead, while nine others were injured. The accident happened as a result of over-speeding.”